Title: Object: Assassination of General Kleber in Egypt
Description: The general clutching a wound in his chest from the dagger of the figure in local dress at left, as a soldier behind raises his sword to attack the murderer, cannonballs scattered on the ground and clouds of smoke indicating fighting below the wall behind; in frame with an urn and swag above; after William Marshall Craig, illustration from 'A New History of the Twenty Years War with France'. 1815 Engraving and etching
Curator's comments: See 1877,1110.21 for title page and curator's comment.
Associated titles: A New History of the Twenty Years War with France
